<div class='row'>
  <div class="span5">
    <div class='row'>
      <h3>Second step</h3>
      <p>
        In controller we created CreateOrderRequest xml file and we sent it to payu.
        In response we receive CreateOrderResposne xml with STATUS and information about
        basic validation.
        In db was created record in model PayuRails::Commission.
        On this page also should be information about checkout and redirection to payu site.
      </p>

      <p>
        <h5>XML response looks like this:</h5>
        <%= @req.response.body %>

        <h5>And commission record:</h5>
        <%= @commission.inspect %>
      </p>

      <p>
        You can use two predefined helper methods for creating hidden form with basic informations
        for payu such a:
        <ul>
          <li>redirect_uri</li>
          <li>response_type</li>
          <li>client_id/pos_id</li>
        </ul>
        For more please check documentation
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <%= payu_login_link @commission, :image => true %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

